Objectives:
       Contains all the necessary Commnads that help to Controal files.

  ⌯⌲ File System Navigation:
        +----------------------------------------------------------------------- +
        |  Command:                  |            Explanation                    |
        + -------------------------- + ----------------------------------------- +
        |    pwd                     |      Shows Current Directory.             |
        |    ls                      |      List Files.                          |
        |    cd <dir>                |      Change directory.                    |
        |    cd ..                   |      Move up one directory.               |
        |    cd ~                    |      Go to home directory.                |
        |    tree                    |      Show directory tree.                 |
        |    touch <file>            |      Create empty file                    |
        |    cat <file>              |      Show file contents                   |
        |    nano <file>             |      Edit file                            |
        |    less <file>             |      Scroll through file                  |
        |   find <path> -name <file> |     Search for a file                     |
        + -------------------------- + ----------------------------------------- +


  ⌯⌲ File & Directory Permissions:
        + -------------------------- + --------------------------------------------------------------- +
        |  Command:                  |            Explanation                                          |
        + -------------------------- + --------------------------------------------------------------- +
        |    mkdir                   |       Create folder                                             |
        |    rmdir <dir>             |       Remove empty folder                                       |
        |    rm <file>               |       Remove file                                               |
        |   rm -r <dir>              |       Delete folder + contents                                  |
        |   cp <src> <dst>           |       Copy file                                                 |
        |  cp -r <src> <dst>         |       Copy directory                                            |
        |  mv <src> <dst>            |       Move/rename                                               |
        |  chmod 755 <file>          |       Owner rwx, Group r-x, Others r-x                          |
        |  chmod u+x <file>          |       Add execute to user                                       |
        |  chmod g-w <file>          |       Remove write from group                                   |
        | chmod o+r <file>           |       Add read for others                                       |
        | chown user <file>          |       Change file owner                                         |
        | chown user:group <file>    |       Change owner + group                                      |
        | chown -R user:group <dir>  |       Recursive change                                          |
        + -------------------------- + --------------------------------------------------------------- +

Note:  Symbol Basics: 
r = read
w = write
x = execute
User / Group / Others → u / g / o

⌯⌲ Package Management:
        + -------------------------- + ------------------------------------------- +
        |  Command:                  |            Explanation                      |
        + -------------------------- + ------------------------------------------- +
        |   sudo apt update          |       Update package lists                  |
        |   sudo apt upgrade         |       Upgrade all Packages                  |
        |   sudo apt install <pkg>   |       Install a package                     |
        |   sudo apt remove <pkg>    |       Remove a package                      |
        |   sudo apt purge <pkg>     |       Remove + config files                 |
        |   apt search <keyword>     |       Search for a package                  |
        |   apt show <pkg>           |       Package info                          |
        |   sudo apt autoremove      |       Clean unused deps                     |
        |   sudo dpkg -i <file.deb>  |       Install .deb                          |
        |   dpkg -l                  |       List installed packages               |
        |   dpkg -r <pkg>            |       Remove package                        |
        |   dpkg -S <file>           |       Find which package owns file          |
        + -------------------------- + ------------------------------------------- +


       
